race.comment: TENNESSEE SPIRIT (10) was heavily backed on debut and bumped into a smart one who jumped an odds-on chance on Tuesday at Ascot. She led them up there and just couldn't fend off the leader. Has the speed to roll across from out wide and with that run under her belt, she can go one better. GABEX (11) flew home last start over 1200m behind a dominant winner and we may have seen that formline work out already today. Back to 1100m today is a slight query, but she maps to hold a closer position this time around and can make her presence felt. DASHING DIVA (12) wasn't beaten far over this course and distance 32 days ago and the form out of that race has worked out nicely. Draw is a niggle, but she's racing well enough to be in the finish. GODLESS STORM (2) is first-up for over 560 days but his recent trial suggests he's not out of this. Watch for market moves. COMMON TOUCH (9) won a trial recently and is not out of this.
